The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has released the fourth public health advisory on the novel coronavirus to Nigerians. Its Director-General Chikwe Ihekweazu, made available a copy of the advisory to the News Agency of Nigeria in Abuja. Ihekweazu said this was an updated advisory on the COVID-19 disease, following confirmation of the first case in Nigeria on the Feb. 27. He said: “Currently, there are four laboratories in NCDC’s molecular laboratory network, with the capacity to test for COVID-19 in Nigeria. These laboratories are sufficiently equipped with reagents and supplies for testing. “NCDC is in contact with all states to increase the index of suspicion to ensure cases are detected early,” he said. Ihekweazu said Nigerians could reduced the risk of COVID-19 by adhering to the following measures:  Coronavirus: NCDC issues 4th advisory to Nigerians Coronavirus: 11 suspected cases tested in Nigeria negative — NCDC No coronavirus in broiler chickens – NCDC